{"version": 2, "width": 120, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1776926270, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/zsh", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "sage — pure bash AI agent orchestrator"}
[0.005142, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[0.005705, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# sage — pure bash AI agent orchestrator (zero frameworks, zero deps beyond bash/jq/tmux)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.707129, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m /home/dyouwang/SageCLI/sage --version\r\n"]
[3.534242, "o", "sage 1.3.0\r\n"]
[6.035812, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m /home/dyouwang/SageCLI/sage init\r\n"]
[6.882331, "o", "\u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m sage initialized at /tmp/tmp.AiMDBhGqWI/sage-demo\r\n"]
[9.383713, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# sage demo scaffolds a working 3-agent fan-out example\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.584738, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m /home/dyouwang/SageCLI/sage demo\r\n"]
[12.43218, "o", "demo: created demo-reviewer\r\n"]
[12.45088, "o", "demo: created demo-tester\r\n"]
[12.469438, "o", "demo: created demo-security\r\n"]
[12.470852, "o", "demo: wrote /tmp/tmp.AiMDBhGqWI/sage-demo/plans/demo-fan-out.yaml\r\n"]
[12.471962, "o", "\r\n  ✨ Demo scaffolded. Try:\r\n    sage ls                        # see your 3 demo agents\r\n    sage plan --run /tmp/tmp.AiMDBhGqWI/sage-demo/plans/demo-fan-out.yaml     # run the fan-out pattern\r\n    sage send demo-reviewer \"hi\"   # talk to one agent\r\n    sage demo --clean              # tear it all down\r\n"]
[16.473545, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# Three agents created, ready to review code in parallel:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[18.674719, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m /home/dyouwang/SageCLI/sage ls\r\n"]
[19.532333, "o", "demo-reviewer\r\ndemo-security\r\n"]
[19.532467, "o", "demo-tester\r\n"]
[22.033795, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# And a plan YAML wired up for fan-out execution:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[24.23486, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m cat /tmp/tmp.AiMDBhGqWI/sage-demo/plans/demo-fan-out.yaml\r\n"]
[25.036529, "o", "# sage demo plan — fan-out pattern\r\n# Run: sage plan --run <this-file>\r\npattern: fan-out\r\ntask: \"Analyze the input and report findings\"\r\ninputs: [demo-reviewer, demo-tester, demo-security]\r\n"]
[29.037707, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# sage acp ls — discover agents from the ACP Registry (live)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[31.247061, "o", "\u001b[1;32m$\u001b[0m /home/dyouwang/SageCLI/sage acp ls | head -12\r\n"]
[32.280005, "o", "  amp-acp                  Amp                  ACP wrapper for Amp - the frontier coding agent\r\n  auggie                   Auggie CLI           Augment Code's powerful software agent, backed by industry-leading context engine\r\n  autohand                 Autohand Code        Autohand Code - AI coding agent powered by Autohand AI\r\n  claude-acp               Claude Agent         ACP wrapper for Anthropic's Claude\r\n  cline                    Cline                Autonomous coding agent CLI - capable of creating/editing files, running commands, using the browser, and more\r\n  codebuddy-code           Codebuddy Code       Tencent Cloud's official intelligent coding tool\r\n  codex-acp                Codex CLI            ACP adapter for OpenAI's coding assistant\r\n  corust-agent             Corust Agent         Co-building with a seasoned Rust partner.\r\n  crow-cli                 crow-cli             Minimal ACP Native Coding Agent\r\n  cursor                   Cursor               Cursor's coding agent\r\n  deepagents               DeepAgents           Batteries-included AI coding and general purpose agent powered by LangChain.\r\n  factory-droid            Factory Droid        Factory Droid - AI coding agent powered by Factory AI\r\n"]
[36.781963, "o", "\u001b[1;36m# That's it. 53 commands, 8 runtimes, 928 tests. Pure bash.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
